The Rotary Club of Asokoro has donated wheelchairs and crutches to members of the Abuja disabled person’s community, located at Karmajiji, Airport Road, Abuja. Leader of the group, Akpa Uchenna, who led members of the club said the gesture was to show love to the physically challenged members of the community in fulfilment of a pledge made during an earlier visit. Responding, the chief of the FCT disabled persons colony,  Alhaji Sulaiman Muhammad Katsina, thanked the club for the  gesture, saying the items donated would assist in alleviating the hardship being experienced by the benefiting members. He also said that a number of projects were executed by Rotary International in the community, apart from distributing food items to them especially during the festive periods.